<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4429] Provide synchronous balanceSwitch()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4429</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently balanceSwitch() doesn&apos;t guarantee that balancer isn&apos;t running upon return.&lt;br/&gt;
During code review of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4213&quot; title=&quot;Support for fault tolerant, instant schema updates with out master&amp;#39;s intervention (i.e with out enable/disable and bulk assign/unassign) through ZK.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4213&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4213&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we found that synchronous behavior for turning off balancer is desired.&lt;br/&gt;
We can add blockingBalanceSwitch() to HMasterInterface upon whose return balancer is guaranteed not running.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
